<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-29T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-29T11:00:00-05:00" n="456" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2631/277: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Frost</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-29T11:00:00-05:00">March 29, 1938—11
                                a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>26. Your telegrams 34, 35 and 36, March 21, 22, and 24. The Department is
                            considering the Chilean exchange proposal. For your own information, the
                            proposal does not at first glance appear acceptable, but a definite and
                            detailed reply will be sent you in a few days after receipt of your air
                            mail despatch 930.<note n="36" xml:id="d456fn36">Not printed.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>